            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">9.104-6</ph> Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d535e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d543e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
					          </p>
					          <ol id="d535e23" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d543e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Before awarding a contract in excess of the simplified acquisition threshold, the contracting officer shall review the performance and integrity information available in the Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System (FAPIIS), (available at <xref href="http://www.ppirs.gov"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">www.ppirs.gov</xref>, then select FAPIIS), including FAPIIS information from the System for Award Management (SAM) Exclusions and the Past Performance Information Retrieval System (PPIRS).</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d543e39" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                In accordance with <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 2313(d)(3)</xref>, FAPIIS also identifies–</p>
							              <ol id="d535e48" class="- topic/ol ">
								                <li class="- topic/li ">
									                  <p id="d543e52" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
										                    An affiliate that is an immediate owner or subsidiary of the offeror, if any (see <xref href="FAR-i1064305.dita#i1064305"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">52.204-17</xref>, Ownership or Control of Offeror); and</p>
								                </li>
								                <li class="- topic/li ">
									                  <p id="d543e64" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
										                    All predecessors of the offeror that held a Federal contract or grant within the last three years (see <xref href="FAR-id165VE00099X.dita#id165VE00099X"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">52.204-20</xref>, Predecessor of Offeror).</p>
								                </li>
							              </ol>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d543e80" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
					          </p>
					          <ol id="d535e86" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d543e90" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                When making a responsibility determination, the contracting officer shall consider all the information available through FAPIIS with regard to the offeror and any immediate owner, predecessor, or subsidiary identified for that offeror in FAPIIS, as well as other past performance information on the offeror (see <xref href="FAR-i1074222.dita#i1074222"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  42.15</xref>).</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d543e102" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                For evaluation of information available through FAPIIS relating to an affiliate of the offeror, see <xref href="FAR-i1116122.dita#i1116122"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">9.104-3</xref>(c).</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d543e114" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                For source selection evaluations of past performance, see <xref href="FAR-i1108601.dita#i1108601"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15.305</xref>(a)(2). Contracting officers shall use sound judgment in determining the weight and relevance of the information contained in FAPIIS and how it relates to the present acquisition.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d543e126" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Since FAPIIS may contain information on any of the offeror's previous contracts and information covering a five-year period, some of that information may not be relevant to a determination of present responsibility, e.g., a prior administrative action such as debarment or suspension that has expired or otherwise been resolved, or information relating to contracts for completely different products or services..</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d543e135" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Because FAPIIS is a database that provides information about prime contractors, the contracting officer posts information required to be posted about a subcontractor, such as trafficking in persons violations, to the record of the prime contractor (see <xref href="FAR-i42_1503.dita#i42_1503"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">42.1503</xref>(h)(1)(v)). The prime contractor has the opportunity to post in FAPIIS any mitigating factors. The contracting officer shall consider any mitigating factors posted in FAPIIS by the prime contractor, such as degree of compliance by the prime contractor with the terms of FAR clause <xref href="FAR-i1056535.dita#i1056535"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-50</xref>.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d543e152" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            If the contracting officer obtains relevant information from FAPIIS regarding criminal, civil, or administrative proceedings in connection with the award or performance of a Government contract; terminations for default or cause; determinations of nonresponsibility because the contractor does not have a satisfactory performance record or a satisfactory record of integrity and business ethics; or comparable information relating to a grant, the contracting officer shall, unless the contractor has already been debarred or suspended-</p>
					          <ol id="d535e158" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d543e162" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Promptly request such additional information from the offeror as the offeror deems necessary in order to demonstrate the offeror’s responsibility to the contracting officer (but see <xref href="FAR-i1115236.dita#i1115236"
                              base="i1115236"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">9.405</xref>); and</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d543e174" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Notify, prior to proceeding with award, in accordance with agency procedures (see <xref href="FAR-i1115383.dita#i1115383"
                              base="i1115383"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">9.406-3</xref>(a) and <xref href="FAR-i1115521.dita#i1115521"
                              base="i1115521"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">9.407-3</xref>(a)), the agency official responsible for initiating debarment or suspension action, if the information appears appropriate for the official’s consideration.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d543e191" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The contracting officer shall document the contract file for each contract in excess of the simplified acquisition threshold to indicate how the information in FAPIIS was considered in any responsibility determination, as well as the action that was taken as a result of the information. A contracting officer who makes a nonresponsibility determination is required to document that information in FAPIIS in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1116277.dita#i1116277"
                        base="i1116277"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">9.105-2</xref>(b)(2).</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
		    </conbody>
